The new HBO series Watchmen is a superhero show that deals with serious themes of race and trauma.
“That’s the magic of genre, the magic of fiction,” Buckell says in Episode 393 of the Geek’s Guide to the Galaxy podcast.
“You’re like, ‘My god, I can’t believe this was put on television.’ This is the most wild, unique, incredible show.
And the only people who still think of him as human are Laurie and Angela, these two women who have loved him.
So to me the show didn’t stop talking about race, it just started talking about it in a different medium.”More Great WIRED Stories